entries.meaning: The wing of a bat, or its shape.
examples: The junk was nearer, beating in toward the island, her brown batwing sail suddenly tall and terribly conspicuous against the sky.

entries.meaning: Several South or Southeast Asian species of tailless dark swallowtail butterflies in the genus Atrophaneura.
An area of flabby fat under a person's arms.
A long sleeve with a deep armhole, tapering toward the wrist.
One of a pair of swinging doors which typically do not lock nor cover the full vertical range of the doorway (leaving a large gap at the top and bottom), common especially in saloons.
(often attributive) An exercise or posture on the stomach wherein a dumbbell row or lateral raise is performed.

verbs.description: batwing (third-person singular simple present batwings, present participle batwinging, simple past and past participle batwinged)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive, Internet slang) To kill or murder; to cause the untimely demise of someone.
